{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/compare/2fda61fac6c9cbd43dfc58cd0ff069282b5835e0...7097e5b793de68880ace8413f3be3ccd9d6d7e3c", "html_url": "https://github.com/apache/hadoop/compare/2fda61fac6c9cbd43dfc58cd0ff069282b5835e0...7097e5b793de68880ace8413f3be3ccd9d6d7e3c", "permalink_url": "https://github.com/apache/hadoop/compare/apache:2fda61f...apache:7097e5b", "diff_url": "https://github.com/apache/hadoop/compare/2fda61fac6c9cbd43dfc58cd0ff069282b5835e0...7097e5b793de68880ace8413f3be3ccd9d6d7e3c.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/apache/hadoop/compare/2fda61fac6c9cbd43dfc58cd0ff069282b5835e0...7097e5b793de68880ace8413f3be3ccd9d6d7e3c.patch", "base_commit": {"sha": "2fda61fac6c9cbd43dfc58cd0ff069282b5835e0", "node_id": "C_kwDOAWVWldoAKDJmZGE2MWZhYzZjOWNiZDQzZGZjNThjZDBmZjA2OTI4MmI1ODM1ZTA", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Steve Loughran", "email": "stevel@cloudera.com", "date": "2021-09-29T12:42:07Z"}, "committer": {"name": "GitHub", "email": "noreply@github.com", "date": "2021-09-29T12:42:07Z"}, "message": "HADOOP-17851. S3A to support user-specified content encoding (#3498)\n\n\r\nThe option fs.s3a.object.content.encoding declares the content encoding to be set on files when they are written; this is served up in the \"Content-Encoding\" HTTP header when reading objects back in.\r\n\r\nThis is useful for people loading the data into other tools in the AWS ecosystem which don't use file extensions to infer compression type (e.g. serving compressed files from S3 or importing into RDS)\r\n\r\nContributed by: Holden Karau", "tree": {"sha": "a6b40cda5cf768afa7796e6bfa2ed02e7804a09c", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/git/trees/a6b40cda5cf768afa7796e6bfa2ed02e7804a09c"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/git/commits/2fda61fac6c9cbd43dfc58cd0ff069282b5835e0", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": true, "reason": "valid", "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsBcBAABCAAQBQJhVF8fCRBK7hj4Ov3rIwAACfgIA